Modules.Delgath's Lament:
{{Main|Delgath's Lament}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Chris Weeda]], [[Catherine Keene]], and the Universe Construction Company
* '''Released:''' January 1999

Modules.Tomb of the Unknown:
{{Main|Tomb of the Unknown}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Steve Hardinger]], [[Gene Luster]], [[Agnes Thompson]], and [[Robert Wiese]]
* '''Released:''' February 1999

Modules.Another Serious Matter:
{{Main|Another Serious Matter}}
{{Quote|It's time to rise, go forth, and conquer once again. The Wizards Guild needs your services for another far-flung mission.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Paul Pederson]]
* '''Released:''' February 1999
''Part 2 of the "The Saga of the Diabolical Grasp".''

Modules.In Memory of Evermeet:
{{Main|In Memory of Evermeet}}
{{Quote|Children have been disappearing throughout Ravens Bluff. The daughter of an influential merchant has gone missing and he wants you to find her.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Kevin Blake]]
* '''Released:''' February 1999

Modules.Rage:
{{Main|Rage (adventure)}}
{{Quote|A dwarven village destroyed. A squad of Griffin Knights missing. Thane Uldred Deepaxe desperately needs your aid. Are you brave enough to answer his call?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Todd M. Smart]]
* '''Released:''' March 1999
''Part 1 of "The New Darkness".''

Modules.The Underground:
{{Main|The Underground}}
{{Quote|Prison life is hard. There are things in the dark which make it harder. Lady Blacktree needs you to solve a problem for her husband which could affect the safety of everyone in Ravens Deep.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Chris Ruester]]
* '''Released:''' February 1999
''Part 2 of the "Red Threats" series.''

Modules.Where in Ravens Bluff is Madison Connor?:
{{Main|Where in Ravens Bluff is Madison Connor?}}
{{Quote|A kidnapped friend leads to a very interesting adventure in far-away places. Can you track one of the city's sneakier adventurers and save her from&hellip;}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel Llewellyn]]
* '''Released:''' February 1999

Modules.Shadows Rising:
{{Main|Shadows Rising}}
{{Quote|The gangs of Ravens Bluff are uniting under a single banner, destroying all who will not bow to a mysterious shadow leader. Will you put a stop to their criminal plans?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erik Mona]]
* '''Released:''' March 1999
''Part 1 of the "Gang Wars" series.''

Modules.Friend or Foe?:
{{Main|Friend or Foe?}}
{{Quote|Good news at last for the forces of Ravens Deep. A party of Svirfneblin have approached Lord Blacktree and are interested in an alliance. Diplomacy&hellip; in the Underdark?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Todd Smart]]
* '''Released:''' March 1999
''Part 5 of the "HUD" series.''

Modules.Civic Duty:
{{Main|Civic Duty}}
{{Quote|Ravens Bluff is a rich city teeming with adventurers. Do you have what it takes to be one? You will soon find when you are asked to perform your civic duty. This is an introduction to the Living City campaign and is intended for new characters only.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Bob Tomihiro]]
* '''Released:''' March 1999

Modules.Knight and the Living Dead:
{{Main|Knight and the Living Dead}}
{{Quote|A Voice of the Past calls to the Adventurers of Ravens Bluff to assist with her own past. Recommended for Knights, City Watch, and clergy of Tyr.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' April 1999
''Sequel to ''[[A Knight in the Big House]]''.''

Modules.Quatlebar:
{{Main|Quatlebar (adventure)}}
{{Quote|The ambassador of Cormyr has lost his quatlebar, and you have to find it to avoid a diplomatic incident. Only problem&mdash;what is a quatlebar?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gary Labrecque]]
* '''Released:''' March 1999

Modules.The Guns of Azzagrat:
{{Main|The Guns of Azzagrat}}
{{Quote|People have been disappearing from Ravens Bluff without a trace. Clearly magic is involved, but how far will the search take you? Ebon Tendrils weave their way into the city of Ravens, with revenge as their dark goal. The party must aid the wizards guild in tracking down a very special scout, and leading him on a journey beyond the heavens.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erik Mona]]
* '''Released:''' April 1999
''Episode Two of "Ebon Tendrils".''

Modules.The Quest for Fire:
{{Main|The Quest for Fire}}
{{Quote|A letter was sent to the Thultyrl from a priest of Kossuth requesting permission to build a shrine in the Temple District. As with all other requests of this nature, the request was denied pending proper submission through the Quorum of Temples. The response received was unacceptable, especially since a shrine to his most-hated rival was already supported within the city. So a curse was placed upon the city: All those who venerate the name of Istishia will lose the privilege of fire. It is up to the PCs to appease Kossuth and bring fire back to Procampur.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' April 1999

Modules.Rightful Property:
{{Main|Rightful Property}}
{{Quote|A wealthy merchant wants you to recover some stolen property for him and he is willing to pay. Sounds simple right?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Frank Timar]] and [[Erika Timar]]
* '''Released:''' April 1999

Modules.Salvation:
{{Main|Salvation}}
{{Quote|You are given the opportunity to enter the Abyss to free a wrongly imprisoned soul you do not know. To do so, you must enter the Abyss with nothing, not even the clothes on your back. If you are killed your own soul might be forced to serve a tanar'ri lord for eternity. Sometimes it's not for the excitement, adventure or reward. Sometimes, it's for real.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Joe Masdon]]
* '''Released:''' April 1999

Modules.Stoneheart:
{{Main|Stoneheart}}
{{Quote|You are sent into the mountains near Ravens Bluff to gather some herbs for a village that needs them to fight of a disease. What possible adventure could occur in the mountains?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Sean Duff]]
* '''Released:''' May 1999

Modules.Crawl 2: Another Temple, Another Time:
{{Main|Crawl 2: Another Temple, Another Time}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Keith Polster]]
* '''Released:''' May 1999

Modules.Everything Dies:
{{Main|Everything Dies}}
{{Quote|Low-tier: A summons from a member of the Wizards Guild of Ravens Bluff leads you to accept a mission to find a runaway fiancée, It sounds easy&hellip; but then again who is to say what lies ahead of you?<br />
High-tier: The Wizards Guild of Ravens Bluff summons you for a mission of extreme importance. You are asked to investigate an island through to be the source of a mysterious force that might be behind the disappearances of whole villages. This is an extremely dangerous mission&mdash;definitely not for the weak-hearted!}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Larry Douglas]]
* '''Released:''' June 1999

Modules.A Ticket to Midnight:
{{Main|A Ticket to Midnight}}
{{Quote|Numerous trips to the Astral Plane have discovered a Great Machine in a former githyanki fortress. Rumors abound as to its connection to the Heart of Bane and the threat that it may pose to the entire Vast. It falls to the heroes of Ravens Bluff to discover the truth of the matter.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erich Schmidt]]
* '''Released:''' June 1999
''Adventure #1 in the "High-Level Planar Campaign".''

Modules.Revenge of the Evermen:
{{Main|Revenge of the Evermen}}
{{Quote|As the Shadow Leader's Crow's End gang wars continue, the Green Knives, uneasy allies to the City Watch, find themselves in need of help. The past of one of their masters was quite a mess, and messes have a way of catching up with you in the City of Ravens.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erik Mona]]
* '''Released:''' June 1999
''Part 2 of the "Gang Wars" series.''

Modules.Before Its Time:
{{Main|Before Its Time}}
{{Quote|Why would you miss a party celebrating the grand re-opening of a tavern? Especially when the food and drink is free! Then the hostess asks for a simple favor. You are adventurers, right?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Rick Brill]]
* '''Released:''' June 1999

Modules.Dog Days of Summer:
{{Main|Dog Days of Summer}}
{{Quote|Something is amiss in Ravens Bluff today. An excess of robberies, a dearth of dogs, and all the cats are happy. Can you allow this to happen?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[J. Allan Fawcett]] and [[Jean Rabe]]
* '''Released:''' June 1999

Modules.I'm Your Bane:
{{Main|I'm Your Bane}}
{{Quote|After being hired by a ranger from Tantras, the adventurers find themselves traveling into a mountainous region in the name of Lathander to search for a lost temple of Bane. They are to stop the minions of Bane at all costs.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[John Wyatt]]
* '''Released:''' June 1999

Modules.Grimm Revelations:
{{Main|Grimm Revelations}}
{{Quote|As things get worse in the Jewel of the Vast, the Star Guard clamps down on crime. Sometimes, the crimes are made up. A mysterious patron invites you to a meeting, which leads you deep into the political intrigue currently afoot in Procampur.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Dan Cooper]] and the Universe Construction Company
* '''Released:''' July 1999
''Part 10 of the "Cracked Jewel Saga".''

Modules.The Forgotten Land:
{{Main|The Forgotten Land}}
{{Quote|You receive a summons from Lady Catherine Blacktree requesting your assistance with a secret diplomatic mission to a far away land. The letter states that if you accept this assignment, you will be briefed on some important cultural practices to follow while there. Cultural practices? Where in the world could this mission be sending you?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Larry Douglas]]
* '''Released:''' July 1999

Modules.A Hope and a Prayer:
{{Main|A Hope and a Prayer}}
{{Quote|A lesson in history taught by one who has much to learn.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' July 1999

Modules.The Mines of Sarbreen:
{{Main|The Mines of Sarbreen}}
{{Quote|An exploration of the former mines of Clan Brightsword and a far distant outpost called the Redoubt.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jeffrey J. Morrison]]
* '''Released:''' July 1999
''Part 7 of the "HUD" series.''

Modules.Ruff Knight in Ravens Bluff:
{{Main|Ruff Knight in Ravens Bluff}}
{{Quote|The dark tidings of the city is just the beginning as a foul wizard or magical aberration forces Ravens Bluff to go to the dogs.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Daniel S. Donnelly]]
* '''Released:''' July 1999

Modules.The Witch of the Mists:
{{Main|The Witch of the Mists}}
{{Quote|One of the more unusual calls for assistance you have encountered during your career as an adventurer in Ravens Bluff leads you to a meeting of The Fellowship of Exalted Adventurers. The Fellowship has fallen on tough times and your assistance is required to halt the declining membership. This is an adventure for heroes: mercenaries and other greed-driven characters are unlikely to enjoy the event.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Ed Gibson]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999

Modules.The Lacquered Chest:
{{Main|The Lacquered Chest}}
{{Quote|You have been summoned to the Celestial Gateway Emporium to investigate a strange antiquity, a lacquered chest of ancient Kara-Turan design. Will your actions lead to honor or will you become an affront to the ancestors?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Lawrence Ramirez]] and Lab Rat Play Testing
* '''Released:''' August 1999

Modules.Heir Un-Apparent:
{{Main|Heir Un-Apparent}}
{{Quote|Chief Prelate Relarn Dayspring searches for heirs of the blood of a famous Lathandrian paladin, and evil from the past stirs its head again.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jeffrey Scott Meyers]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999
''Part 2 of the "Cycle of Cyric".''

Modules.The Challenge of Children:
{{Main|The Challenge of Children}}
{{Quote|A request for help for the Children's Vocational Center comes from a surprising source. A roleplaying adventure for those that like unusual situations.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Stephanie Zuiderweg]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999

Modules.Three Coins in a Well:
{{Main|Three Coins in a Well}}
{{Quote|In the plane of Ysgard there is a place where all questions can be answered. It is the Well of Knowledge. The heroes of Ravens Bluff are called on by the Ministry of Art to travel to the Well and discover more information about the Great Machine.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erich Schmidt]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999
''Adventure #2 in the "High-Level Planar Campaign".''

Modules.The Isle of the End:
{{Main|The Isle of the End}}
{{Quote|How the mighty have fallen. You have been put in charge of the Ravens Deep beautification detachment. Our new svirfneblin ally, King Durglewrathinda Murgleishenblin, has expressed a desire to visit Ravens Deep and he will be here in less than a week! He is bringing with him several of his ministers to negotiate a Trade and Mutual Defense Treaty. Field Marshal Blacktree wants everything shipshape by the
time the King gets here. However, an unlikely messenger arrives with a troubling dispatch. So much [for] clean-up detail; time to go back to work.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Dave Sreniawski]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999
''Part 8 of the "HUD" series.''

Modules.Summer Festival in Mossbridges:
{{Main|Summer Festival in Mossbridges}}
{{Quote|Join your friends in the Living City for the Summer Festival in Mossbridges. Take yourself to the Wizard's Guild, Clerical Circle, City Watch, and more. Enter a sporting competition and test your mettle. If the contests are too tame, you can enter the arena and battle fearsome monsters with your bare hands. Expect some surprises from around the Realms as well. Who knows what else you will find?}}
* '''Designer(s):'''
* '''Released:''' August 1999

Modules.See No Evil:
{{Main|See No Evil}}
{{Quote|You are hired for the simple job of making sure that a valuable piece of art doesn't get stolen. Of course things never stay that simple.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Andrew Jaremkow]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999

Modules.To Boldly Go... One Last Time:
{{Main|To Boldly Go... One Last Time}}
{{Quote|Do you have what it takes to save an entire realm from certain doom? Do you have the brawn, or more importantly, do you have the brains?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[John Bentas]] and [[Maurice Ouellette]]
* '''Released:''' August 1999
''Part 3 of the "Boldly" series.''

Modules.The Fallen Knight:
{{Main|The Fallen Knight}}
{{Quote|A knight turned to evil takes you to Hlintar and into the start of a strange quest to find out what is corrupting knights of the Vast.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Sean Duff]]
* '''Released:''' September 1999
''Part 1 of the "Corruptor Series".''

Modules.The Moon:
{{Main|The Moon}}
{{Quote|When the Church of Selûne asks adventurers to find a valued member, can anything but foul play be expected?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Victor Long]]
* '''Released:''' September 1999

Modules.See How They Run:
{{Main|See How They Run}}
{{Quote|A merchant's daughter needs your help finding her lost brother. Sounds simple enough, until you find out that the rest of the family cannot know you are involved. What is going on?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Andrew Jaremkow]]
* '''Released:''' October 1999

Modules.All the World's a Stage:
{{Main|All the World's a Stage}}
{{Quote|Something is rotten in Drazen Humfrey's theater, and, for once, it's not just the plays! All things will become clear once you take the stage yourselves.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Morrie Mullins]] and [[Christina Nichols]]
* '''Released:''' October 1999

Modules.Cuckolds and Mussels:
{{Main|Cuckolds and Mussels}}
{{Quote|You are invited to join some High Society members of Ravens Bluff as they say farewell to a retiring Captain in the Ravens Bluff Navy. Sea travel required and don't forget your dancing shoes!}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Mark Templeton]]
* '''Released:''' October 1999

Modules.Dawning of a New Day:
{{Main|Dawning of a New Day}}
{{Quote|You are summoned to the Roost regarding a matter of great importance. Further details will be provided when you arrive.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David Samuels]]
* '''Released:''' October 1999

Modules.For a Few Zhents More:
{{Main|For a Few Zhents More}}
{{Quote|Once more the city is in need of adventurers. But is this more babysitting than anything else? What could possibly go wrong?}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[David P. Santana]]
* '''Released:''' October 1999
''Part 2 of the "Flight of Arrows" series.''

Modules.The Return:
{{Main|The Return (adventure)}}
{{Quote|One of the newly resettled farms outside of the city walls was burned to the ground last night. The City Watch, under pressure from the Mayor, needs adventurers to investigate independently from the watch.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gary Labrecque]]
* '''Released:''' October 1999
''Sequel to ''[[Quatlebar (adventure)|Quatlebar]]''.''

Modules.Beautification Day:
{{Main|Beautification Day}}
{{Quote|The Church of Sune Firehair is sponsoring Beautification Day, a day to clean up and beautify Ravens Bluff, co-sponsored by the churches of Hanali Celanil and Sheela Peryroyl. A party is promised afterwards at the temple of Lliira. A mysterious, unsigned note arrives the day before, warning you to attend and stop those planning on sabotating Beautification Day&mdash;the safety of Ravens Bluff could depend on it.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gary Labrecque]]
* '''Released:''' November 1999
''Part 1 of the "Torr" series.''

Modules.Shadowed Paths:
{{Main|Shadowed Paths}}
{{Quote|It's been a lazy few weeks in Ravens Bluff, with pleasant weather and little trouble in the days of mid-summer. You've had time to relax, catch up on work or friends, and actually enjoy life for a change. In fact, things are really starting to look up when you receive an invitation to a party at the Grand Griffon Inn! If past experience is any indication, this could be the start of something interesting.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Nick Perch]]
* '''Released:''' November 1999
''Part 3 of the "Black Hand" series.''

Modules.In the Hall of the Mountain Mage:
{{Main|In the Hall of the Mountain Mage}}
{{Quote|An elven princess calls to you in a dream. Answering brings you into a strange ancient world and leaves you with the problem of getting out. But not answering would leave her to a dire fate.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Roger Rhodes]]
* '''Released:''' November 1999

Modules.Stone and Steel:
{{Main|Stone and Steel}}
{{Quote|The case of the Great Machine has been cracked. Ravens Bluff Elite has been asked to start cracking its mysteries.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Erich Schmitt]] and [[George Fulda]]
* '''Released:''' November 1999
''Adventure #3 in the "High-Level Planar Campaign".''

Modules.Starry Eyes:
{{Main|Starry Eyes}}
{{Quote|Traveling Tormish bring word to Ravens Bluff that the village of Maerstar is in need of adventurers. Someone, or something, has been slaying the village's prized riding horses. They have been unable to spot the foe, let alone defeat it. A long journey like this one is bound to bring great adventure, and unknown danger.}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Gregory A. Dreher]]
* '''Released:''' November 1999

